'''''Mirna''-class patrol boat''' (also known as '''Type 171''') is a class of eleven [[patrol vessel]]s built for the [[Yugoslav Navy]] in the [[Kraljevica Shipyard]] from [[1979]] to [[1985]]. During the [[Croatian War of Independence]] and the dissolution of [[Breakup of Yugoslavia|SFR Yugoslavia]], most of the vessels were relocated to [[Montenegro]] except for four boats that were captured or damaged by [[Croatian Armed Forces|Croatian forces]] and later entered service with the [[Croatian Navy]].

All ship were originaly named after [[mountain]]s in the former Yugoslavia.

